I recently saw [Vitaly Friedman][1] demo a great CSS solution I wasn&#39;t aware of. The idea is to apply the `content` property to the broken image. Normally `:after` or `:before` do not apply to images, but when they&#39;re broken, they&#39;re applied.

    &lt;img src=&quot;nothere.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;add alternative text here&quot;&gt;
