The correct way to do this is with the [`break-inside` CSS property](https://www.w3.org/TR/css-break-3/#break-within):
```css
.x li {
    break-inside: avoid-column;
}
```
Unfortunately, as of October 2021, [this is still not supported in Firefox](https://caniuse.com/mdn-css_properties_break-inside_multicol_context_column) but [it is supported by every other major browser](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/break-inside). With Chrome, I was able to use the above code, but I couldn&#39;t make anything work for Firefox ([See Bug 549114](https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=549114)).

