There is a very nice and cool way to make a background image work like an `img` element so it adjust its `height` automatically. You need to know the image `width` and `height` ratio. Set the `height` of the container to 0 and set the `padding-top` as percentage based on the image ratio.

It will look like the following:

    div {
        background-image: url(&#39;http://www.pets4homes.co.uk/images/articles/1111/large/feline-influenza-all-about-cat-flu-5239fffd61ddf.jpg&#39;);
        background-size: contain;
        background-repeat: no-repeat;
        width: 100%;
        height: 0;
        padding-top: 66.64%; /* (img-height / img-width * container-width) */
                    /* (853 / 1280 * 100) */
    }

You just got a background image with auto height which will work just like an img element. Here is a working prototype (you can resize and check the div height): https://jsfiddle.net/w3mpr1Lv/

