**August 2021 update:** My original answer used Html.fromHtml(String), which was deprecated in API 24. The alternative [fromHtml(String,int)][1] form is suggested as its replacement. 

FROM_HTML_MODE_LEGACY is likely to work... but one of the other flags might be a better choice for what you want to do.

On a final note, if you&#39;d prefer to render Android Spanned text suitable for use in a TextView using **Markdown** syntax instead of HTML, there are now multiple thirdparty libraries to make it easy including https://noties.io/Markwon.

  [1]: https://developer.android.com/reference/android/text/Html#fromHtml(java.lang.String,%20int)

