To supplement the original answer &amp;ndash; somewhat belatedly &amp;ndash; I&#39;m editing to show the use of `clip-path`, which has replaced the now-deprecated `clip` property.

The `clip-path` property allows a range of options (more-so than the original `clip`), of:

* `inset` &amp;mdash; rectangular/cuboid shapes, defined with four values as &#39;distance-from&#39; `(top right bottom left)`.
* `circle` &amp;mdash; `circle(diameter at x-coordinate y-coordinate)`.
* `ellipse` &amp;mdash; `ellipse(x-axis-length y-axis-length at x-coordinate y-coordinate)`.
* `polygon` &amp;mdash; defined by a series of `x`/`y` coordinates in relation to the element&#39;s origin of the top-left corner. As the path is closed automatically the realistic minimum number of points for a polygon should be three, any fewer (two) is a line or (one) is a point: `polygon(x-coordinate1 y-coordinate1, x-coordinate2 y-coordinate2, x-coordinate3 y-coordinate3, [etc...])`.
* `url` &amp;mdash; this can be either a local URL (using a CSS id-selector) or the URL of an external file (using a file-path) to identify an SVG, though I&#39;ve not experimented with either (as yet), so I can offer no insight as to their benefit or caveat.

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    div.container {
      display: inline-block;
    }
    #rectangular {
      -webkit-clip-path: inset(30px 10px 30px 10px);
      clip-path: inset(30px 10px 30px 10px);
    }
    #circle {
      -webkit-clip-path: circle(75px at 50% 50%);
      clip-path: circle(75px at 50% 50%)
    }
    #ellipse {
      -webkit-clip-path: ellipse(75px 50px at 50% 50%);
      clip-path: ellipse(75px 50px at 50% 50%);
    }
    #polygon {
      -webkit-clip-path: polygon(50% 0, 100% 38%, 81% 100%, 19% 100%, 0 38%);
      clip-path: polygon(50% 0, 100% 38%, 81% 100%, 19% 100%, 0 38%);
    }

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;div class=&quot;container&quot;&gt;
      &lt;img id=&quot;control&quot; src=&quot;http://lorempixel.com/150/150/people/1&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;container&quot;&gt;
      &lt;img id=&quot;rectangular&quot; src=&quot;http://lorempixel.com/150/150/people/1&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;container&quot;&gt;
      &lt;img id=&quot;circle&quot; src=&quot;http://lorempixel.com/150/150/people/1&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;container&quot;&gt;
      &lt;img id=&quot;ellipse&quot; src=&quot;http://lorempixel.com/150/150/people/1&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;container&quot;&gt;
      &lt;img id=&quot;polygon&quot; src=&quot;http://lorempixel.com/150/150/people/1&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

[JS Fiddle demo](http://jsfiddle.net/davidThomas/36tg0one/), for experimentation.

